I'm guessing the script is French.  Yeah, with no money denomination I didn't think they were postage stamps; they're just perforated like the lick-and-stick stamps my kids used to have, and look to have been torn from a bigger sheet.  They're numbered, apparently in a series.

People collect all sorts of things.  Why not these?

PS:  Babelfish says the print on the bottom says &quot;Handling of the divining rod from old times&quot;
